    <item>
      <title>What Is FDE?</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/20260511-what-is-fde/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 11:36:30 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/20260511-what-is-fde/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;FDE stands for Forward Deployed Engineer, a role first systematized by Palantir. While a traditional product engineer builds a single feature to serve many customers, an FDE provides the diverse range of capabilities required by a single customer.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The distinction can be illustrated by a specific scenario: a pre-sales engineer’s job ends when the customer says, &amp;ldquo;This looks like it should work,&amp;rdquo; whereas an FDE’s job begins when the customer says, &amp;ldquo;Then let’s get it running.&amp;rdquo; If your code is live in a customer&amp;rsquo;s production environment and you’re the one handling on-call issues at midnight, you are an FDE.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
